WEBVTT

00:06.441 --> 00:09.444
- Previously,
on "Deadly Class"...

00:09.487 --> 00:10.706
- Step away from the goat
and put your hands in the air.

00:10.749 --> 00:12.186
- I was just spreading
some love.

00:12.229 --> 00:13.448
[laughs]
- Legacy hazing

00:13.491 --> 00:15.058
is a time-honored tradition.

00:15.102 --> 00:16.712
- [screams]
- You don't belong with us.

00:16.755 --> 00:18.627
Come to that dance,
you'll regret it.

00:18.670 --> 00:20.281
[suspenseful music]

00:20.324 --> 00:22.587
Welcome to the
Legacy Committee, sweetheart.

00:22.631 --> 00:24.763
Miss Rat, 1987.

00:24.807 --> 00:27.549
- You're right to be angry.
Let's burn them down.

00:27.592 --> 00:29.899
- [groans]

00:29.942 --> 00:37.080
♪

00:47.786 --> 00:50.224
- [slurping]

00:56.839 --> 00:59.798
[Iron Maiden's "Wasted Years"
playing from speakers]

00:59.842 --> 01:03.280
♪

01:03.324 --> 01:04.803
- ♪ Yeah

01:04.847 --> 01:08.285
- ♪ From the coast of gold

01:08.329 --> 01:11.636
♪ Across the seven seas

01:11.680 --> 01:14.639
♪ I'm traveling on
- Suck it!

01:14.683 --> 01:17.642
- ♪ Far and wide

01:17.686 --> 01:20.471
♪ But now it seems

01:20.515 --> 01:23.474
♪ I'm just a stranger
to myself ♪

01:23.518 --> 01:25.259
♪ And all the things
I sometimes do ♪

01:25.302 --> 01:26.782
- Look out!

01:26.825 --> 01:30.829
♪ It isn't me
but someone else ♪

01:30.873 --> 01:33.310
♪ I close my eyes

01:33.354 --> 01:36.226
♪ And think of home

01:36.270 --> 01:38.837
♪ Another city goes by

01:38.881 --> 01:42.493
♪ In the night

01:42.537 --> 01:44.321
♪ Ain't it funny how it is?

01:44.365 --> 01:46.671
- Yeah, I just did
the "Risky Business."

01:46.715 --> 01:48.804
Full tighty-whities.

01:48.847 --> 01:50.458
When in Rome.

01:50.501 --> 01:53.722
No, that movie sucked.

01:53.765 --> 01:56.638
Can't get behind some rich kid
trying to hide the fact

01:56.681 --> 01:59.902
that he cracked his Mom's
Fabergé egg.

01:59.945 --> 02:02.992
First, he gets
a high-end call girl,

02:03.035 --> 02:05.255
crashes his Dad's Porsche,

02:05.299 --> 02:07.953
and I'm supposed to care
if his brothel's a success?

02:07.997 --> 02:10.869
Yes, the scene
with Rebecca De Mornay

02:10.913 --> 02:13.176
on the subway
is hotter than shit,

02:13.220 --> 02:14.569
and I'd bone that.

02:14.612 --> 02:16.832
I'm not talking structure.

02:16.875 --> 02:20.444
I'm talking
a general relatability.

02:20.488 --> 02:23.317
If--if you'd just listen!

02:24.535 --> 02:26.494
Fuck you, Mom!

02:26.537 --> 02:28.626
[doorbell rings]

02:28.670 --> 02:31.716
Guarantee the answer's a no.

02:35.851 --> 02:38.245
Whoa, brother.

02:38.288 --> 02:40.508
Your face is fucked.

02:40.551 --> 02:43.511
[twangy rock music]

02:43.554 --> 02:48.211
♪

02:48.255 --> 02:49.734
[blade slices]

02:49.778 --> 02:51.954
♪

02:51.997 --> 02:53.782
- [exhaling sharply]

02:53.825 --> 03:00.832
♪

03:04.793 --> 03:06.577
- Fuck.

03:06.621 --> 03:10.581
Teddy, just hang in there, bud.

03:10.625 --> 03:12.801
I'm coming.

03:12.844 --> 03:15.847
[indistinct chatter]

03:20.287 --> 03:23.333
[ominous electronic music]

03:23.377 --> 03:24.726
♪

03:24.769 --> 03:27.076
- Chico.

03:27.119 --> 03:31.515
♪

03:31.559 --> 03:34.039
- I'll see you
in 48 hours, baby.

03:34.083 --> 03:36.999
♪

03:37.042 --> 03:38.957
Stop, man.

03:39.001 --> 03:41.351
- [grunts]

03:41.395 --> 03:42.744
Viktor did nothing wrong.

03:42.787 --> 03:44.006
Hey!

03:44.049 --> 03:46.269
I am pillar of community!

03:46.313 --> 03:53.320
♪

03:57.759 --> 04:00.022
[coin clinking]

04:10.032 --> 04:11.990
♪

04:12.034 --> 04:15.472
[coin rattles]

04:20.042 --> 04:23.872
[door closes]
- [scoffs]

04:26.135 --> 04:28.659
What is this?

04:28.703 --> 04:30.313
- Prolonged confinement

04:30.357 --> 04:33.621
designed for
behavioral rectification.

04:33.664 --> 04:35.710
[whispering]
Detention.

04:39.061 --> 04:41.672
- What did you do?

04:55.599 --> 04:57.471
- Sip?

04:59.734 --> 05:01.126
[door opens]

05:04.391 --> 05:05.870
- Master Lin.

05:05.914 --> 05:08.743
All due respect,
this must be an oversight

05:08.786 --> 05:11.702
'cause I didn't do--

05:11.746 --> 05:13.182
Yeah.

05:13.225 --> 05:14.662
Fine.

05:14.705 --> 05:16.011
But if I'm getting hit
for fighting,

05:16.054 --> 05:17.752
shouldn't Willie's ass
be in here, too?

05:17.795 --> 05:20.450
- All Viktor did was invite
rodent girl to dance.

05:20.494 --> 05:23.932
- All I did was punch a Nazi,
inbred, debutante bi--

05:23.975 --> 05:26.717
- You all committed
the cardinal sin.

05:26.761 --> 05:28.415
You were caught.

05:31.418 --> 05:32.680
- Ah!

05:32.723 --> 05:34.812
- Agoge.

05:34.856 --> 05:38.686
Spartan instruction
that molded petulant Greek boys

05:38.729 --> 05:42.429
into the greatest warriors
in the world.

05:42.472 --> 05:44.866
It had three basic tenets--

05:44.909 --> 05:47.956
conformity, discipline,

05:47.999 --> 05:52.526
and commitment to Sparta
over one's own interests.

05:52.569 --> 05:54.615
[tense music]

05:54.658 --> 05:55.920
- You want to keep that hand?

05:57.748 --> 06:00.098
- You chose
your baser instinct.

06:00.142 --> 06:01.143
Rivalry.

06:01.186 --> 06:04.146
♪

06:04.189 --> 06:06.148
You will spend your weekend

06:06.191 --> 06:09.543
locked in this room...

06:09.586 --> 06:12.720
contemplating
my disappointment.

06:12.763 --> 06:19.770
♪

06:26.168 --> 06:28.126
[lock clicks]

06:28.170 --> 06:30.259
♪

06:30.302 --> 06:33.262
[mellow rock music playing
over speakers]

06:33.305 --> 06:37.962
♪

06:38.006 --> 06:40.138
[indistinct chatter]

06:40.182 --> 06:41.792
[door closes]

06:41.836 --> 06:48.843
♪

06:57.547 --> 06:59.506
[door bells jingle]

06:59.549 --> 07:02.509
[indistinct chatter]

07:02.552 --> 07:05.512
[dramatic music]

07:05.555 --> 07:07.992
♪

07:08.036 --> 07:10.995
[rock music]

07:11.039 --> 07:13.650
♪

07:13.694 --> 07:15.783
- We live our lives behind
these fictitious ideas

07:15.826 --> 07:18.046
of what we think
other people will accept.

07:18.089 --> 07:19.830
♪

07:19.874 --> 07:22.920
Barricaded behind masks,
honing our act.

07:22.964 --> 07:24.618
♪

07:24.661 --> 07:26.184
When people laugh,

07:26.228 --> 07:29.274
we learn and repeat
what amuses them.

07:29.318 --> 07:32.843
When they respect us...

07:32.887 --> 07:37.587
when we're given their
validation, we feel secure.

07:37.631 --> 07:39.937
But over time,
the person down underneath

07:39.981 --> 07:43.332
the social training
becomes unrecognizable...

07:43.375 --> 07:45.552
lost.

07:45.595 --> 07:48.990
Our act becomes the truth.

07:49.033 --> 07:50.818
And the truth becomes
some residual

07:50.861 --> 07:52.646
of the weak person we were

07:52.689 --> 07:54.865
before we learned how
to fit in.

07:54.909 --> 07:57.302
- [breathing steadily]

07:57.346 --> 08:01.611
♪

08:01.655 --> 08:03.613
- Hey, Vik, you got the time?

08:03.657 --> 08:05.615
- Very funny, Nancy boy.

08:05.659 --> 08:07.704
[sighs]

08:08.879 --> 08:11.099
Is Swatch.

08:11.142 --> 08:12.883
Top American style.

08:12.927 --> 08:14.755
- That's smart.

08:14.798 --> 08:17.627
In case you break
the other two.

08:17.671 --> 08:20.587
- Fuck Lin
and his Trojan bullshit.

08:20.630 --> 08:21.892
Once I get what I want
from this joint,

08:21.936 --> 08:23.851
I'm gonna stick a machete
up his ass.

08:23.894 --> 08:25.635
- Now he pipes up.

08:25.679 --> 08:27.245
45 minutes after he left.

08:27.289 --> 08:29.204
- You're the one that I should
be carving up, Arguello.

08:29.247 --> 08:31.902
Your queefy dart bullshit
got us thrown in here, yeah?

08:31.946 --> 08:34.252
- You think the queefy dart
was faster than The Flash?

08:34.296 --> 08:37.081
- No, but he could
out-queef Superman for sure.

08:45.046 --> 08:48.049
[siren wailing in the distance]

08:50.268 --> 08:52.880
- Hey, look, I ain't got
no kinds of beef

08:52.923 --> 08:54.185
with your people.

08:54.229 --> 08:56.231
- You think I'm here
to jump you?

08:56.274 --> 08:57.841
[siren continues wailing]

08:57.885 --> 09:00.061
- Me and Chico ain't exactly
sweet on each other.

09:00.104 --> 09:03.194
- No one's sweet on Chico.

09:03.238 --> 09:05.980
- I thought you two were--
- I need a passport.

09:08.156 --> 09:10.071
- Ain't that
a cartel specialty?

09:10.114 --> 09:11.812
- They can't know.

09:11.855 --> 09:14.423
- "They can't"--
All right, hold up.

09:14.466 --> 09:17.121
I ain't trying to get mixed up
in no lover's quarrel bullshit.

09:17.165 --> 09:19.820
- Chico's locked up
for two days.

09:19.863 --> 09:21.909
This is my chance
to get away from him.

09:24.302 --> 09:26.261
- That bad?

09:26.304 --> 09:28.263
- [sighs]

09:28.306 --> 09:30.265
[tense music]

09:30.308 --> 09:33.137
Just do this for me.

09:33.181 --> 09:35.923
Please.

09:35.966 --> 09:42.973
♪

09:49.371 --> 09:51.678
- All I'm saying
is what's been done to you

09:51.721 --> 09:52.809
determines who you'll be.

09:52.853 --> 09:54.289
- I'm who I choose to be.

09:54.332 --> 09:56.857
- So, shitty parenting
made Ted Bundy start

09:56.900 --> 09:58.206
shish-kebabing coeds?

09:58.249 --> 10:00.121
- Bundy's dad,
also his grandfather--

10:00.164 --> 10:01.426
what could go wrong?

10:01.470 --> 10:03.124
- Shit, nobody stuck a finger
up my ass.

10:03.167 --> 10:04.821
I'm as deadly as they come.

10:04.865 --> 10:06.257
- Well, by that logic,

10:06.301 --> 10:09.086
I made Viktor
three fingers more deadly.

10:09.130 --> 10:11.045
- She is lying.

10:11.088 --> 10:12.786
My "shoofla" is exit only.

10:12.829 --> 10:14.396
- Whatever broken shit
is inside of us

10:14.439 --> 10:16.267
is there the day we're born.

10:16.311 --> 10:17.660
People are what they are.

10:17.704 --> 10:20.097
- Wait, what's a "shoofla"?

10:21.142 --> 10:22.752
[pan sizzling]

10:22.796 --> 10:24.232
- How long are you staying?

10:24.275 --> 10:27.322
- Uh, till I can fix things,
kemosabe.

10:27.365 --> 10:29.977
- You should have called.
I didn't get enough groceries.

10:30.020 --> 10:32.022
[dish clatters]

10:36.723 --> 10:38.333
[pan clatters]

10:38.376 --> 10:40.291
- Ugh. [spits]
Gah!

10:40.335 --> 10:41.771
The milk's curdled.

10:41.815 --> 10:43.120
- It's not milk, it's mayo.

10:43.164 --> 10:45.166
- What?
- They were out.

10:45.209 --> 10:48.256
- [spits]
Safeway was out of milk?

10:48.299 --> 10:50.824
[door opens, closes]

10:50.867 --> 10:53.914
- He lost it again, didn't he?

10:56.090 --> 11:00.224
- [grunts] You don't like it,
Private School,

11:00.268 --> 11:03.053
you don't have to eat it.

11:03.097 --> 11:06.056
[dark music]

11:06.100 --> 11:10.931
♪

11:10.974 --> 11:13.455
- I propose we conduct
an experiment--

11:13.498 --> 11:16.719
evolve past
the chimpanzee stage.

11:16.763 --> 11:17.894
[hippie drawl]
And open ourselves

11:17.938 --> 11:20.810
to free love,
crunchy grooves,

11:20.854 --> 11:24.335
and drinking the soul's sweet,
sweet stardust.

11:24.379 --> 11:26.555
Let's at least pretend
to like each other.

11:26.598 --> 11:28.513
- Torture Town, USA.

11:28.557 --> 11:30.733
- Two bags of chips
for two days.

11:30.777 --> 11:32.213
That's torture.

11:32.256 --> 11:34.128
- There's enough
monosodium glutamate in there

11:34.171 --> 11:35.129
to kill a rhino.

11:35.172 --> 11:36.913
- Mm, MSG.

11:36.957 --> 11:39.263
- The monks are gonna bring
more food, right?

11:39.307 --> 11:40.874
- One box per detention.

11:40.917 --> 11:42.353
- [sighs]

11:42.397 --> 11:44.573
Lucky one of my superpowers
is starving.

11:44.616 --> 11:45.966
- What is other?

11:46.009 --> 11:47.445
Sitting on man's "horkum"?
[laughs]

11:47.489 --> 11:50.492
- You know, if it's junk food
you desire,

11:50.535 --> 11:54.104
we could break
into the vaults of Valhalla.

11:58.543 --> 12:01.329
There's a chest...

12:01.372 --> 12:03.810
this big...

12:03.853 --> 12:07.074
full of diabetes-inducing
treats,

12:07.117 --> 12:09.903
among other
glorious contraband.

12:09.946 --> 12:12.079
- This is your brain on drugs.

12:12.122 --> 12:14.124
The confiscation room
is impenetrable, man.

12:14.168 --> 12:16.126
- Like Saya's panties.

12:16.170 --> 12:17.867
- It's been done...

12:17.911 --> 12:21.044
once.

12:21.088 --> 12:23.394
Lin's cornucopia
was pried open

12:23.438 --> 12:26.615
by a group of industrious
detention attendees.

12:26.658 --> 12:30.184
The robbers inscribed
their deeds on the rooftop.

12:30.227 --> 12:34.449
"The golden door
on the secret floor."

12:34.492 --> 12:36.320
- I bet that's where
my sword is.

12:36.364 --> 12:39.584
♪

12:39.628 --> 12:43.284
[shouts, grunts,
pounding on door]

12:43.327 --> 12:47.331
♪

12:47.375 --> 12:50.334
[grunting and pounding on door
continue]

12:50.378 --> 12:56.166
♪

12:57.951 --> 13:00.214
You're such a spaz.

13:00.257 --> 13:01.955
- Oh, God, it's so obvious.

13:01.998 --> 13:03.913
- What?

13:03.957 --> 13:06.089
- You want to get married
and have babies

13:06.133 --> 13:08.004
and hump on the washing machine
all day and--

13:08.048 --> 13:10.050
- Or you're my pledge,

13:10.093 --> 13:11.834
and I'm obligated
to keep you alive,

13:11.878 --> 13:14.576
which means anything you do
comes back on me.

13:14.619 --> 13:17.187
It's like being tethered
to a large, dumb thing

13:17.231 --> 13:20.930
that is sinking in quicksand.

13:20.974 --> 13:23.890
Hence our current situation.

13:23.933 --> 13:30.940
♪

13:33.029 --> 13:36.424
[lock clicks]

13:36.467 --> 13:38.600
♪

13:38.643 --> 13:40.863
- So he is cop man,

13:40.907 --> 13:42.430
or he is cop robot?

13:42.473 --> 13:44.171
- Half and half.

13:44.214 --> 13:46.042
- Which is robot half?

13:46.086 --> 13:47.565
- No, man.

13:47.609 --> 13:50.177
He's a dude
in a big old metal suit.

13:50.220 --> 13:51.613
- It's not a suit.

13:51.656 --> 13:53.267
They replaced his body
with cybernetics.

13:53.310 --> 13:55.965
The "robo" part
keeps his brain alive.

13:56.009 --> 13:59.273
- This is very confusing film.

13:59.316 --> 14:01.666
- So if Lin catches me
smoking crack

14:01.710 --> 14:03.625
or running naked
through Chinatown--

14:03.668 --> 14:06.236
- We're both dead.

14:06.280 --> 14:09.587
- Yet here we are
breaking his rules.

14:09.631 --> 14:12.112
- I have my own rules--
Bushido.

14:12.155 --> 14:13.635
Your honor lives
in your sword,

14:13.678 --> 14:16.203
and I'm not leaving my honor
in a closet

14:16.246 --> 14:18.466
next to some Hot Pockets.

14:18.509 --> 14:21.034
- [whispering]
Hey, shh.

14:21.948 --> 14:24.080
[dishes clattering]

14:24.124 --> 14:26.474
[bell dings]

14:42.490 --> 14:46.233
- You skeptics don't deserve
the spoils that await.

14:46.276 --> 14:48.278
But...

14:48.322 --> 14:50.193
I'm a generous captain.

14:53.283 --> 14:56.243
[lock clicks]

14:56.286 --> 15:00.073
- Oh...
- [gasps]

15:00.116 --> 15:02.640
[devious music]

15:02.684 --> 15:05.426
- [laughing]
- Wow.

15:05.469 --> 15:07.428
- What the hell?

15:07.471 --> 15:10.083
- Oh, shit.
- Oh, nice.

15:10.126 --> 15:12.085
- Party.

15:12.128 --> 15:14.609
[all chuckle]
- Whoo-hoo.

15:14.652 --> 15:17.481
- Oh, nice.

15:17.525 --> 15:20.658
- There are explosives in here.
Let's blow some shit up.

15:20.702 --> 15:23.487
♪

15:23.531 --> 15:25.968
- It's not here.

15:26.012 --> 15:28.753
- Where else could it be?

15:28.797 --> 15:31.408
[dishes clatter,
siren wailing in the distance]

15:31.452 --> 15:33.802
[door opens, bells jingle]

15:33.845 --> 15:37.153
[foreboding music]

15:37.197 --> 15:39.764
[door closes]

15:39.808 --> 15:46.641
♪

15:50.819 --> 15:53.735
[both grunting]

15:56.825 --> 16:00.133
[helmet clatters]

16:00.176 --> 16:02.004
- You're waking the wolf,
Arguello.

16:02.048 --> 16:04.137
- Ooh.
- I'm gonna jack you up.

16:04.180 --> 16:06.139
[both grunting]

16:06.182 --> 16:08.663
- Hey.
- [coughing]

16:08.706 --> 16:10.839
[blows landing]

16:10.882 --> 16:13.189
- [exhales deeply]

16:13.233 --> 16:15.148
[blows land, thud]

16:15.191 --> 16:17.802
Viktor has been
looking for you.

16:17.846 --> 16:21.502
- I get the Pop Rocks,
and I get the Mountain Dew,

16:21.545 --> 16:23.286
but what's the cheese for?

16:23.330 --> 16:27.682
- Blowing....your...mind.

16:27.725 --> 16:30.076
[Viktor groans]

16:30.119 --> 16:32.165
- Oh, it's like riding
a cheese dragon

16:32.208 --> 16:35.298
through a forest
of delicious sweets.

16:35.342 --> 16:36.821
Mmm.

16:42.871 --> 16:45.004
- What?

16:45.047 --> 16:47.049
- Just doesn't seem like
you're having much fun.

16:47.093 --> 16:49.965
- If I lose my katana,
my life is over.

16:50.009 --> 16:52.620
- What do you think's gonna
happen--Lin's pawning it?

16:52.663 --> 16:55.884
It'll turn up.
- How do you know?

16:55.927 --> 16:58.017
- Things always work out.

16:58.060 --> 17:00.802
- Vietnam, cancer kids,
Sonny and Cher,

17:00.845 --> 17:03.065
and weren't you homeless?

17:03.109 --> 17:05.198
- Yeah, it's just something
my dad used to say.

17:05.241 --> 17:08.549
It's not 100%, I guess.

17:08.592 --> 17:10.899
It's probably closer to ten.

17:10.942 --> 17:14.250
- I didn't even get
to use this puppy.

17:19.081 --> 17:20.169
- Jesus!

17:20.213 --> 17:23.216
[ball hissing, laughter]

17:27.133 --> 17:29.222
- Misery loves company.

17:29.265 --> 17:31.615
But the second,
lesser-known part is:

17:31.659 --> 17:35.619
Company doesn't much care
for misery.

17:35.663 --> 17:38.622
[rock music]

17:38.666 --> 17:44.759
♪

17:44.802 --> 17:47.109
- It's a little smaller
than yours,

17:47.153 --> 17:50.112
but this is guaranteed
to cheer you up.

17:50.156 --> 17:57.119
♪

17:58.251 --> 18:00.122
[engine revving]

18:00.166 --> 18:02.777
- Hundred bucks says
she doesn't make it.

18:02.820 --> 18:04.866
♪

18:04.909 --> 18:06.259
[engine revving]

18:06.302 --> 18:08.913
