37:20.412 --> 37:23.632
because he wanted me
to be great.

37:23.676 --> 37:26.418
I hated him for it,
but it worked.

37:26.461 --> 37:30.813
♪

37:30.857 --> 37:35.470
I didn't think it was gonna
feel this way.

37:35.514 --> 37:37.559
- It's not supposed
to feel good.

37:37.603 --> 37:44.566
♪

37:44.610 --> 37:47.352
- At Shabnam's party...

37:47.395 --> 37:51.181
- When you were trying
to kiss me?

37:51.225 --> 37:53.706
- You clearly misunderstood.

37:53.749 --> 38:00.408
♪

38:29.350 --> 38:30.699
- My goodness.

38:30.743 --> 38:33.659
- We raised Shabnam
better than this.

38:33.702 --> 38:36.531
- At least he's made
a friend or two.

38:36.575 --> 38:38.794
- Teenagers need boundaries.

38:38.838 --> 38:41.319
I'm calling that school
first thing tomorrow.

38:41.362 --> 38:43.495
- [clears throat]

38:43.538 --> 38:46.498
[tense music]

38:46.541 --> 38:48.587
What school?

38:48.630 --> 38:51.720
♪

38:51.764 --> 38:54.636
- Hey, you hear
about what happened?

38:54.680 --> 38:55.855
Jesus.

38:55.898 --> 38:57.726
[door closes]

38:57.770 --> 38:58.858
- It's just another
Saturday night

38:58.901 --> 39:00.381
at the Bennett house.

39:00.425 --> 39:02.514
My fault for going back.

39:02.557 --> 39:03.906
- Your dad?

39:03.950 --> 39:06.256
- An after-school special
come to life.

39:06.300 --> 39:07.954
Read a book about it.

39:07.997 --> 39:10.043
Said abusive parents are like
a human version of the flu.

39:10.086 --> 39:13.873
Don't go around them
unless you want to get sick.

39:13.916 --> 39:16.528
[grunts softly]
- Why'd you go back?

39:16.571 --> 39:19.574
- My little brother.

39:19.618 --> 39:23.012
He said some creeps have been
coming around the house again.

39:26.538 --> 39:29.889
You want to know why I go
to this academy of the damned?

39:29.932 --> 39:32.326
My dad owes the Mob,
like, a million bucks,

39:32.370 --> 39:33.762
so they're training me

39:33.806 --> 39:36.417
to go work for them
to pay off his debt.

39:36.461 --> 39:38.724
Got home and found out he's
into a whole nother crew now.

39:38.767 --> 39:40.987
- Mm.
Gambling?

39:41.030 --> 39:44.730
- It must be, like,
super fun, right?

39:44.773 --> 39:46.949
So I call him out.

39:46.993 --> 39:49.430
He goes nuts,
starts to push me.

39:49.474 --> 39:50.866
I go to get my shit to leave,

39:50.910 --> 39:53.434
he follows me down
the hallway, pushing me,

39:53.478 --> 39:56.437
screaming.

39:56.481 --> 39:57.743
[scoffs]

39:57.786 --> 39:59.919
"Turn your back on me,
sonny boy?"

39:59.962 --> 40:01.573
"Little Lord Fauntleroy
coming home

40:01.616 --> 40:03.444
"from private school to judge?

40:03.488 --> 40:06.099
"Bitch and moan--
that's all you ever do.

40:06.142 --> 40:08.406
Just another victim!"

40:09.668 --> 40:10.930
[sniffles]

40:10.973 --> 40:12.975
So he's red in the face.

40:13.019 --> 40:15.761
Standing in the doorway,
won't let me leave.

40:15.804 --> 40:17.589
My mom tries to stop him.

40:17.632 --> 40:20.461
"Gene!
Gene, stop it!"

40:20.505 --> 40:21.854
[breathing heavily]

40:21.897 --> 40:23.769
So he throws her into a wall,
as you do.

40:23.812 --> 40:26.685
Family photos go everywhere.

40:26.728 --> 40:30.471
I went to stop him, but, uh...

40:30.515 --> 40:33.474
Gene's a big guy.

40:33.518 --> 40:36.912
He--he, uh...

40:36.956 --> 40:38.653
Got on top of me.

40:38.697 --> 40:41.787
[somber music]

40:41.830 --> 40:45.138
He has a lot of rings...

40:45.181 --> 40:48.010
big gold ones.
[sniffles]

40:48.054 --> 40:51.492
I remember watching them
coming down.

40:51.536 --> 40:53.842
[breathing shakily]

40:53.886 --> 40:55.801
He got tired pretty fast.

40:55.844 --> 40:58.499
20 years of cigarettes
and Schlitz.

40:58.543 --> 40:59.935
♪

40:59.979 --> 41:02.764
I had an opening.
I got on top of him.

41:02.808 --> 41:04.549
♪

41:04.592 --> 41:06.638
But I couldn't do it.

41:06.681 --> 41:08.422
♪

41:08.466 --> 41:10.424
Why is that?

41:10.468 --> 41:13.601
After everything
he's done to us...

41:13.645 --> 41:16.038
I couldn't hit him.

41:16.082 --> 41:18.388
[stammering]

41:18.432 --> 41:21.522
- Hey, I think it shows
you're still intact.

41:21.566 --> 41:23.524
You're just a kid
who still loves his dad.

41:23.568 --> 41:26.658
- No.
[cries]

41:26.701 --> 41:28.529
[breathing shakily]

41:28.573 --> 41:30.836
That's not it.

41:30.879 --> 41:34.579
♪

41:34.622 --> 41:36.668
My brother's a kid.

41:36.711 --> 41:39.105
He's a really,
really good kid.

41:39.148 --> 41:42.761
[sniffles, sobs]

41:42.804 --> 41:46.547
My mom, my brother...

41:46.591 --> 41:48.810
♪

41:48.854 --> 41:51.857
They're not gonna survive him.

41:51.900 --> 41:54.076
- What can we do?

41:54.120 --> 41:55.730
♪

41:55.774 --> 41:58.559
- Take a road trip.

41:58.603 --> 42:00.039
To Vegas.

42:00.082 --> 42:02.737
- "A-a road trip"?

42:02.781 --> 42:05.087
[suspenseful music]

42:05.131 --> 42:08.003
- To kill my dad.

42:08.047 --> 42:13.966
♪
